history.content:
Hello all!

 

The Engineering Student Council, in collaboration with Engineers for a Sustainable World, is hosting a virtual faculty panel, “COVID-19: Building More Sustainable and Ethical Systems” on April 29th (Wednesday)! This is an exciting opportunity to get to speak to Berkeley professors who are experts in fields that are critical in fighting the current global pandemic.

The panel will be held over Zoom from 7:00-8:30 pm PST - students who wish to participate must have a Berkeley email and fill out the following RSVP form, also found at tinyurl.com/esc-facultypanel-2020. ONLY students who fill out the form will be eligible to receive the Zoom link.

A full list of participating faculty will be officially released on April 15th. Please check out our Facebook event for exciting updates! 

 

We hope to see you there (online)!

 

Warm regards,


The Engineering Student Council & Engineers for a Sustainable World
